Word Pairs with Explanation
Car – Vehicle
These words are semantically similar because a car is a type of vehicle. They belong to the same category.
Happy – Joyful
These are synonyms, meaning they have almost the same meaning and express positive emotions.
Big – Large
Both words describe size and are similar in meaning, so they are semantically related.
Hot – Cold
These words are opposites (antonyms), but still semantically related because they represent extremes of temperature.
Teacher – Student
These words are related in context (education). They are not similar but are connected in meaning.

Explanation
Semantic similarity refers to how closely two words are related in meaning. Words can be:
Similar (synonyms) → same meaning
Opposite (antonyms) → opposite meaning but related
Contextually related → used in the same domain

